# Government Tender Announcement

### Title
CSC Fresh Produce

### Registration Number
WS4202248643-Doc4202353808

### Solicitation Number
WS4202248643

### Edition Number
8th Edition

### Tender Information

| Date | Information |
| --- | --- |
| Post Date | October 3, 2023 |
| Tender Closing Date | December 8, 2023, 14:00 EST |
| Expected Contract Start Date | December 1, 2023 |
| Expected Contract End Date | October 31, 2024 |

### Business Requirements

We are seeking a qualified service provider to supply fresh produce to the Correctional Service of Canada (CSC).

### Invites Standing Offer

The CSC is inviting service providers to submit a standing offer to supply fresh fruit and vegetables.

### Trade Agreements

This procurement is open to vendors who meet the specified requirements and are presently registered under one of the following trade agreements:  North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA), Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership (CPTPP), Canada-Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA), Canada-European Union Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA).

### Regions of Delivery

The regions for the delivery of fresh produce include Manitoba, Alberta, and Saskatchewan.

### Contracting Entity

The contracting entity for this procurement is the Department of Public Works and Government Services.

### Contact Information

Rina Marsland
Public Works and Government Services Canada
 Phone: Not available
 Email: [rina.marsland@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca](mailto:rina.marsland@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca)
 Address: Not available

### Notice Information

Tender Description: <https://discovery.ariba.com/rfx/17615509?extsite=MTc2MTU1MDlfQU4wMTQ4NDA1MDk5Mg==>

Please find all information related to this tender under the original source link.

Selected regions include, but are not limited to:

* *50300000 Fresh fruits*
* *50400000 Fresh vegetables*

All interested and qualified bidders are required to submit their bids by the closing date specified, with the exceptions as provided in the solicitation documents.

The stipulated tender closing time has changed. Vendors are hereby advised to disregard the closing times provided on the Ariba Discovery posting response deadline and CanadaBuys posting closing time. All responses and all requirements must be submitted within the revised schedule
